And the main vertices and
charges which are relevant.

8
00:00:31,140 --> 00:00:34,010
Weak interactions, in fact,
do not deserve their name.

9
00:00:34,010 --> 00:00:37,871
Their apparent weakness at low energy is
due to the fact that they are transmitted

10
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:38,911
by heavy particles,

11
00:00:38,911 --> 00:00:44,085
the neutral Z, and
the charged W± bosons.

12
00:00:44,085 --> 00:00:47,570
Their propagator weakens the amplitude
at low momentum transfer.

13
00:00:49,175 --> 00:00:51,570
Their coupling constant, g and
g’, on the other hand,

14
00:00:51,570 --> 00:00:54,870
are of comparable magnitude
as the electric charge e.

15
00:00:54,870 --> 00:00:58,470
Indeed, they are connected by
the condition of electro-weak unification,

16
00:00:58,470 --> 00:01:00,291
which involves the Weinberg angle theta_W.

17
00:01:01,410 --> 00:01:03,920
Its value is close to 30 degrees.

18
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:08,270
So instead of three coupling constants,
there's only one and an angle.

19
